Cell.Text: The Thalmor hunted us down, remember? It wasn't exactly great for recruitment. | But we have a headquarters of a sort now. We'll rebuild the Blades. Someday.

Node.Caption: FreeformSkyHavenTempleADelphineStartTopic: So this is all the Blades? Two people?

Cell.Text: [S] If you find anyone you think would make a good recruit, I can certainly take a look at them. | Remember, though, being a Blade is a lifelong commitment. Their loyalty has to be with us once they're in.

Cell.Text: Are you sure? I'll need to ask them to take an oath to leave their old life behind and stay here from now on.
You want this one to become a Blade? You're sure?

Cell.Text: Very well. I'll do the oath later. Let's just get 'em geared up and ready to fight.
Very well. He seems like a fighter to me. I'll give him the oath.
Very well. She seems like a fighter to me. I'll give her the oath.

Node.Caption: FreeformSkyHavenTempleADelphineFollowerTopic01: I'm sure. The Blades need new members.

Cell.Text: [S] G|If you find any more candidates bring them here.
[S] G|I can handle training one more. After that, I think we'll be ready for a little dragon hunting of our own.
[S] G|That's enough recruits for now. Ask Esbern about the dragon lairs he's been studying. We'll have the recruits do some hunting with you.

[S] I am. The Blades of the 2nd Era hunted down many dragons in there day, and they have records of where the beasts lived. | Only you can truly defeat these monsters, Dragonborn, but you do not have to do so alone. The Blades can help you. | Just ask whenever you're ready to take on a dragon. We will send the Blades to help you fulfill your destiny.
It's quiet for now, Dragonborn. Perhaps later we'll find where one of those serpents is hiding.

Node.Caption: FreeformSkyHavenTempleBEsbernGiveTopic: Delphine mentioned you're studying dragon lairs.
